data.meta_description: Photo of a Jogja batik maker from 1930 from the Leiden University Digital Collection. The process of batik: "The hot and liquid wax is scooped from small wajan (wok) heated upon small stove. The batik craftsperson sometimes blow the spout tip of canting to allow the liquid wax to flow smoothly and to avoid clogging, then they draw the line or dot upon the cloth, applying the liquid wax, following the patterns and images that previously had been drawn using pencil." Source: Wikipedia
